# CODEOWNERS — review gates for the SOCIII platform
#
# This file maps directories to required reviewers. When a Pull Request
# changes files in a directory listed here, GitHub automatically requests
# review from the listed owners and (with branch protection enabled on
# `main`) BLOCKS merging until they approve.
#
# Purpose: creator-published workers can be reviewed quickly by anyone with
# write access; changes to the platform itself (backend, rules engine,
# capability registry, infrastructure config) require Sean's explicit
# review before they merge.
#
# Syntax: each line is `<path-pattern> @<github-username-or-team>`.
# Patterns later in the file override earlier ones for the same path.
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-customizations/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DEFAULT — everything not otherwise specified requires Sean's review
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

*       @seanlcombs

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PLATFORM CORE — explicitly require Sean. These are the moat.
# Even if a future maintainer is added with write access, changes
# in these paths still need Sean's approval.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

