# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CREATOR DIRECTORIES — light-touch review
#
# Each creator owns their own subdirectory under /creators/. PRs that
# change ONLY files inside their own directory get a faster review
# path because the changes can't affect anyone else's worker, the
# platform infrastructure, or the marketplace billing logic.
#
# Note: the maintainer (Sean or a future delegated reviewer) still
# reviews creator PRs before merge, but the bar is "does the worker
# meet the DoD" rather than "does this change compromise platform
# safety." A creator cannot merge their own PR.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Top-level creators directory — Sean owns the structure and the
# templates, but individual creator workspaces are self-managed
# by their creator (see per-creator entries below).
/creators/                      @seanlcombs
/creators/_template/            @seanlcombs

# Per-creator workspaces. Each line below grants the creator review
# privileges over their OWN directory only. Add a new line when you
# onboard a new creator.
#
# Format: /creators/<handle>/    @<their-github-username>

/creators/ruthie/               @seanlcombs    # @ruthie-handle — to be added once Ruthie has GitHub set up
# /creators/<handle>/            @<their-github>

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Notes for setup
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. CODEOWNERS only enforces review requests. To actually BLOCK a merge
#    without the listed owner's approval, enable branch protection on
#    `main` in GitHub settings:
#
#      Settings → Branches → Add rule for `main`
#         → Require a pull request before merging
#         → Require approvals from Code Owners
#         → Require status checks to pass (CI workflows)
#         → Do not allow bypassing the above settings
#
# 2. When you add a new creator, add a line above mapping their
#    /creators/<handle>/ directory to their GitHub username. Until you
#    do, all their PRs route to Sean.
#
# 3. To remove a creator (suspension, departure), comment out their
#    line. They lose review privilege over their own directory; their
#    workspace remains in the repo for historical/audit purposes
#    but they can no longer self-approve changes.
